\section{Introduction}\label{Introduction}

Hidden-sector photons as massive particles having only a tiny
interaction (kinetic mixing) with known particles was suggested in
\cite{Okun} where it has been also emphasized that stellar evolution
can place a strong limit for these species. However recently the
interest to HPs as the candidate for CDM has been revived probably
because the experiments on WIMPS as a paradigm for dark matter
produce negative results what stimulates researchers to look for new
horizons.

